INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (5928, 'enUS', 'I am glad you found your way here today, young $C. The time has come for you to take a large step into a much larger world.$B$BInside each of Cenarius\' children is the call to serve nature. Animals and plants are our friends as well as our charges. We choose to devote our lives as preservers of balance for their sakes as well as our own. Your first step into this world will be to learn of the ways of the bear, and to learn strength of body and heart.$B$BReady yourself!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (5929, 'enUS', 'Dendrite makes another invisible gesture in the air above him as you approach. Another aura of power comes over him, and he smiles ever so slightly.$B$B\"I sense wisdom in you, young one, that was not present when we first met. You gaze upon me with strength and knowing intent, though this intent is yet not focused. You will now learn to focus your strength and adopt the nature of the bear into your work.\"', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (5930, 'enUS', 'Dendrite makes another invisible gesture in the air above him as you approach. Another aura of power comes over him, and he smiles ever so slightly.$B$B\"I sense wisdom in you, young one, that was not present when we first met. You gaze upon me with strength and knowing intent, though this intent is yet not focused. You will now learn to focus your strength and adopt the nature of the bear into your work.\"', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (5941, 'enUS', 'Ah yes, there they are. Together they weave a powerful spell, one that will raise the spirits of Darrowshire.$B$BWith that spell, and with a little luck, we can save Joseph Redpath!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (5942, 'enUS', 'The key fits the lock, and the chest opens...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (5943, 'enUS', 'Not sure it\'s a prosperous proposition to be paying so much money to protect the Gizelton Caravan. Cork and Rigger only make one gold piece a week, but as long as they keep paying for my kodos I can care less how they run their business.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (5944, 'enUS', 'The death of my son at the hands of these monsters will not pass without incident. Take solace in knowing that the Order is reborn.$B$BI now take my place as Highlord of the new Order of the Silver Hand.$B$BThese possessions of my past - they are all that I have to offer for all that you have done. Please, take these as a symbol of my gratitude; all have served me well over the years.$B$BMay we meet again, in better times, and reminisce of days long past... battles hard fought... dreams redeemed.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (5961, 'enUS', 'Surely the Dark Lady does not believe you worthy to meet her champion. You are here to feed my hounds, yes? There could be no other reason for this interruption.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (5981, 'enUS', 'Excellent, $n. Your determination has been duly noted.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6004, 'enUS', 'Well done, $n. I\'m amazed you dealt with them so quickly. Thank you.$B$BI have yet to meet anyone that approves of the Scarlet Crusade and their methods. I believe in the Light as much as anyone else in Stormwind, but they\'ve demonstrated that they only want to kill anyone not loyal to their movement... even innocents.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6021, 'enUS', 'Great, you got him! And I hope you taught his gang a lesson too!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6022, 'enUS', 'Disappointing. I was hoping that I\'d be feeding you to my hounds, instead.$B$B<Nathanos sighs.>$B$BWell, at least they\'ll have something to eat.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6023, 'enUS', 'Thank you, $n. You\'ve been more help than I could have hoped for. The air here just seems to suck my will. I feel tired, and I can tell I\'m not getting any better the longer I\'m here.$B$BI\'m not really sure how I\'m going to infiltrate Hearthglen itself and report on how strong the Scarlet Crusade\'s presence is.$B$BBut that\'s another matter, before you leave, here, take this... as payment for your help. Thank you again.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6024, 'enUS', 'Hameya\'s chest is opened!!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6025, 'enUS', 'You\'ve done it, $n! Thank you!$B$BI\'ll return to Elling... I mean Stormwind as soon as I can. Here, take this coin, it\'s the least I can do for you. You\'re a credit to your people, $n. Thank you and good luck.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6026, 'enUS', 'I can pay you half up front and half when the job is done.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6027, 'enUS', 'The long lost Book of the Ancients! I will ensure this book is passed on to the high council. You\'ve done well today, and for that you are to be thanked... as a hero should be thanked!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6028, 'enUS', 'Very resourceful, Gregor is. He\'s been dealing with the Steamwheedle Cartel for some time now, and has become an expert on the \"art\" of goblin negotiations. Though it\'s true that the goblins\' primary loyalties lie with those who have the largest coin purses, they also know and respect the value of diplomacy. If anything, it provides them with repeat customers...$B$BAt any rate, the Argent Dawn acknowledges you for your effort. Please have this, with our thanks.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6029, 'enUS', 'Resourceful for a human, Gregor is. He\'s been dealing with the Steamwheedle Cartel for some time now, and has become an expert on the \"art\" of goblin negotiations. Though it\'s true that the goblins\' primary loyalties lie with those who have the largest coin purses, they also know and respect the value of diplomacy. If anything, it provides them with repeat customers...$B$BAt any rate, the Argent Dawn acknowledges you for your effort. Please have this, with our thanks.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6030, 'enUS', 'This... this is a very special book you have brought me. I\'d like to tell you that \"special\" in this case means \"unique and quite possibly illuminating\", but that remains to be seen.$B$B\"Ooooooo?\" Who in their right mind thinks this up?$B$BWell now, I\'ve heard of this Umbranse that Gregor spoke of, so this isn\'t without merit. I\'ll do my best to decipher it. As for you... please, have this - courtesy of the Argent Dawn. While you are here, perhaps there are some other things you can aid us with.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6031, 'enUS', 'Ah, you brought the cloth. Such fine material it is!$B$BThank you, $n. You are a true friend. Please accept this in exchange.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6032, 'enUS', 'Ah, very good. This mooncloth will be used for garments sacred to our people. Thank you, $n. Now I will train you.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6041, 'enUS', 'You\'re much darker than I remember. You got that look going for you; the look that says, \'I\'ve been charred by a high explosive bomb.\'$B$B<Smokey laughs.>$B$BAnyhow! Here\'s your cut of the loot. I\'ve thrown in a little something extra to help soothe the burns.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6042, 'enUS', 'It\'s incredible what a little anger and rage can get accomplished.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6066, 'enUS', 'Yes, I do believe you are ready...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6067, 'enUS', 'Yes, I do believe you are ready...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6068, 'enUS', 'Yes, it is time for you to begin your training.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6069, 'enUS', 'Yes, it is time for you to begin your training.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6070, 'enUS', 'Yes, it is time for you to begin your training.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6071, 'enUS', 'Yes, it is time, $C.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6072, 'enUS', 'Yes, it is time, $C.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6073, 'enUS', 'Yes, it is time, $C.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6074, 'enUS', 'Yes, I do believe you are ready, as well....', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6075, 'enUS', 'Yes, I do believe you are ready, as well....', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6076, 'enUS', 'Yes, I do believe you are ready, as well....', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6132, 'enUS', 'My sister Melizza said you\'d be coming. Thanks a lot for getting her out of the jam she was in; it\'s too bad that she\'s already probably found herself in a new one!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6133, 'enUS', 'I trust you did not read the registry. Not even you would do something that idiotic...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6134, 'enUS', 'There it is! Looks like you got some of it on you too. Kinda slimey, eh?$B$BWell, thanks a lot for all the trouble, $n. This stuff will be worth a fortune... if I can convince the centaurs what it is!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6135, 'enUS', 'Excellent work, imbecile. I shall fashion this fur into something you can use.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6136, 'enUS', 'Keep this up and I may have to promote you from imbecile to mental deficient, first class.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6141, 'enUS', 'I received word of aid arriving from the east. Are you the source of these rumors? Have you come here to help the Scarlet Brother in its crusade?$B$BIf so, then listen close...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6142, 'enUS', 'Perfect mon, this is just what the witch doctor told me to do for my headache. He says, \"Mai\'Lahii - go fish. It\'ll make you feel better\"$B$BWell, I feel better already, thanks mon!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6143, 'enUS', 'As sweet as it is hearing the news that the naga have been vanquished, my heart still feels empty. For the rest of my life I will be dedicated to having them all killed.$B$BHere mon, your reward as I promised. It\'s small in comparison to the gratification of knowing the naga fried for their hated act upon my crew.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6144, 'enUS', 'The Grand Crusader sits safely in the Scarlet Bastion while his forces pour into your lands, desecrate your structures and monuments and murder your people.$B$BThe Dark Lady wishes deal with this insect once and for all and I agree. You will become the instrument of the Horde\'s reckoning.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6145, 'enUS', '<Nathanos laughs.>$B$BExcellent! Finally! An opportunity to destroy the Scarlet Oracle!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6146, 'enUS', 'Where have you been? We had thought the Scourge had captured you.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6147, 'enUS', 'The fools! My deception went unnoticed! Prepare yourself, $C. We must strike with cold cunning!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6148, 'enUS', 'They will be reeling from this blow for years! Well done, $n! You have earned not only my respect but also this reward.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6161, 'enUS', 'Chest opens to reveal Rackmore\'s treasure!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6162, 'enUS', 'You bring honor to me for following through with your word. My husband died in battle--he would have been proud of that. But I could not rest until I knew that the creature that has forced me to live my life alone paid for what it had done.$B$BThank you again, $n.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6163, 'enUS', 'I wonder... did it beg for mercy? Could it know what mercy is?$B$B<Nathanos spits.>$B$BI will hang this beast\'s head upon my wall.$B$BYou have earned a spot amongst one of my champions, $n.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6164, 'enUS', 'There it is! And oh my! I forgot how full it was!$B$BThis is a glorious day, $n! Stupendous! Insanely good, I say!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6181, 'enUS', 'You have to get this note to Stormwind? That\'s not a problem, you can take one of my gryphons!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6182, 'enUS', 'After some reports of unusual Forsaken activity in the Eastern Plaguelands, SI:7 agents were dispatched to investigate. The results of that investigation are unsettling.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6183, 'enUS', '<Mathias nods.>$B$BI had faith that Wrynn would send me men and women of honor - the most dedicated soldiers of the Alliance.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6184, 'enUS', 'The first mission will be straight up, $n. You go in, you come out. Recon...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6185, 'enUS', 'Rutger. Fredo. Turyen. All... dead...$B$B<Flint clutches the insignias tightly.>$B$BWhere were they? Did you discover any more information about this monster, the Blightcaller?', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6186, 'enUS', 'An agent of the Forsaken? The champion of the Banshee Queen?$B$B<King Varian Wrynn grimaces.>$B$BRidiculous...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6187, 'enUS', 'It is a tragedy. I think... I believe that our kind is cursed, $n. We are cursed to lose our greatest warriors; our most noble heroes; our most gifted scholars.$B$BWe are indebted to you and I assure you, $n, wherever Nathanos Marris is now, he smiles down upon you.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6261, 'enUS', 'A crate for Westfall, eh? Have you been to Westfall before? If so, then it\'s no problem, my friend. I have plenty of gryphons trained to fly that route!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6281, 'enUS', 'Ah, a note from Quartermaster Lewis? I\'m not surprised he needs more gear. Sentinel Hill is far away, in a land Stormwind has all but forgotten.$B$BWell thank you, $n. Here\'s some money to cover your travel costs.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6282, 'enUS', 'This is most excellent news! Tell me again how you cast fear into the cold hearts of those vile harpies. The Bloodfuries have been dealt a serious blow!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6283, 'enUS', 'Already I feel the anger leave me. What will I do with my time? Knowing evil moves near my land kept my thoughts moving, though now they are silent. Perhaps this is a good thing... maybe now I can focus on the good, as all tauren should.$B$BPlease accept this as a reward for your troubles.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6284, 'enUS', 'Good hunting, $n! Besseleth is an old predator in these parts... I will miss her not. Take this reward as a token for being the forest champion.$B$B$B$BPerhaps now many more will travel to Sun Rock Retreat without fearing what lurks in the dark.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6285, 'enUS', 'Great, you brought the armor! We\'ll get this divvied to those who need it immediately.$B$BThank you, $n. Your efforts have been a great help to us. And now that you\'re no stranger to gryphons, I hope you\'ll come and lend your aid to Sentinel Hill often!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6301, 'enUS', 'Ah, $n, you have the Gaea seeds. Watch and see how the blessing of the Earthmother can cause even these small kernels of life to bloom and flourish.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6321, 'enUS', 'Ah, an order for supplies. You will want to take this to the Undercity, no doubt. And quickly, for Brill must not be left under stocked.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6322, 'enUS', 'This crate must reach Brill quickly? That is easily done; our bats fly there daily.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6323, 'enUS', 'An order from Brill? Very well. It is an honor to serve those who serve our Dark Lady.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6324, 'enUS', 'Good work, $n. These weapons will ensure our Deathguards don\'t get caught unprepared.$B$BYou have done a valuable service for our Dark Lady.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6341, 'enUS', 'Something for me? I wonder who sent it...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6342, 'enUS', 'Do you need a ride back to Dolanaar?', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6343, 'enUS', 'It sounds like she loved it. Thank you for bringing the book to Sister Aquinne, $n. One of these days, I intend to take her up on her invitation to visit her in Darnassus.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6344, 'enUS', 'That\'s very thoughtful of Nyoma. For a few coins, I can arrange quick transportation to the capital by hippogryph.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6361, 'enUS', 'If you must take these hides to Thunder Bluff, then you have come to the right place.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6362, 'enUS', 'Ah, a new bundle of hides. I will get to work on these immediately!$B$BThank you, brother. You have done me a great service. Here are some coins to pay for your time and travel costs.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6363, 'enUS', 'You need to take this to Bloodhoof Village, eh? That\'s not a problem. If you\'ve already been there and spoken to Tak, then you can take one of my wind riders back to him.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6364, 'enUS', 'Ahanu sent me finished products? Very good. There are many hunters and adventurers in Bloodhoof Village now and business is lively. I am sure I\'ll sell these goods very soon.$B$BThank you for all your efforts, $n. I am in your debt.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6365, 'enUS', 'You have to get this meat to Orgrimmar? That is no problem. For a small fee, my wind rider can take you there.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6381, 'enUS', 'This is great victory for the land. In time, other things will come to pass: the Venture Co. will pack up their buzz saws and axes, the angry fire spirits will calm, and the harpies will be pushed out by the land.$B$BOnly then $n, will Stonetalon be truly at peace.$B$BYou have done well $C; take one of these items as thanks for the new life you have created here today.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6382, 'enUS', 'Welcome to the new frontier, $n. Ashenvale is a land of opportunity, one where a young $C like yourself is able to find boundless chances to prove their mettle. Look around the outpost here, and be sure to travel out to the Zoram Strand, as the Horde has another outpost there as well.$B$BYour presence here tells me that you\'ve come to learn more about the hunt. Listen close, and I will gladly share with you what you need to know.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6383, 'enUS', 'There are three legendary creatures that make up the Ashenvale Hunt; you may seek them and test yourself against their cunning and might. In the process, you will hopefully learn something about yourself. The creatures are: the bear Ursangous, the nightsaber cat Shadumbra, and the hippogryph Sharptalon.$B$BThe creatures of the Ashenvale Hunt are powerful, and you may find that you\'ll need aid in bringing them down. If you should best them, bring me proof of your deed.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6384, 'enUS', 'Oh, wonderful! Those are fine cuts! These are from Grimtak, are they? That orc sure knows his way into a lady\'s heart...$B$BOh, I can\'t wait to cook it. But not too much! Meat is best served rare, don\'t you think?', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6385, 'enUS', 'You have to get this to Razor Hill in Durotar? Yes, I can get you there...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6386, 'enUS', 'Hah! I guess she liked it! Nothing brings red to a lady\'s cheeks like a big, juicy steak!$B$BThank you, $n. You\'ve done me a great service. Here is some money for your trouble, and don\'t be surprised if I invite you to my wedding!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6387, 'enUS', 'You have to get this to Ironforge, eh? For a small fee I can put you on the back of one of my gryphons, and it\'ll take you there. How does that sound?', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6388, 'enUS', 'You have to get these to Kharanos, eh? That won\'t be a problem. As long as you\'ve already been to Kharanos and spoken to Brolan Galebeard, then you can take one of my gryphons back to him.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6389, 'enUS', 'Haha! Thank you, $n! You\'ve done it! My father\'s spirit can now rest and I can live in peace.$B$BThank you again. If there is anything I can do for you, please, just ask.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6390, 'enUS', 'Thank you, $n. Here, take this coin. I\'m sorry it\'s not more, but try to take some joy in helping destroy the Scarlet Crusade\'s efforts!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6391, 'enUS', 'Ah, the lastest list of Gremlock\'s best pupils. I have a batch of honorary cleavers ready to go. I just need to engrave the names of the students...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6392, 'enUS', 'You brought the cleaver. Great! I\'ll get these to my students. I\'m sure they\'re eager to use them on some fresh boar meat.$B$BThank you for your help, $n. I am in your debt, but I hope this money will at least cover your travel costs.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6393, 'enUS', 'The water spirits within me bubble with the excitement. $n, you have given me a glorious victory to report to the Tribunal of the Tides.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6394, 'enUS', 'Great, you got it! Thanks a lot, $n. This is my favorite pick! Now if my peons ever finish chopping down these trees, maybe we can find a nice cave to mine!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6395, 'enUS', 'You have done a good deed today, $n. Although our struggle against the Scourge continues, let us hope that Marla and Samuel will find peace together in their final resting place.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6401, 'enUS', 'My goodness, my niece Kaya is alive! That is good news indeed. Thank you, $n.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6421, 'enUS', 'Ah... Yes! That\'s it; the Resonite crystals have a trace of Earthen magic. The kobolds must have dug deep uncovering an Earthen.$B$BLegend states that the Earthen are creatures created by the Titans. They were used to create the land our feet walk on. This most definitely is a threat that cannot be ignored.$B$B<Mor\'rogal shakes his head.>$B$BPerhaps I can enchant these ore samples to use against this kobold plot.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6441, 'enUS', 'These are perfect, $n! Thanks for helping me out!$B$BOh, and this is for your time...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6442, 'enUS', 'We could use more of your kind around here, $n. Thank you for your help.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6461, 'enUS', 'Sweet, mon! Good news, perhaps we will have fewer unwanted dinner guests tonight.$B$BMany thanks, $n. We are forever in your debt.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6462, 'enUS', 'You found them! Thank you! Thank you, $n! You do not know how great a thing you have done for me.$B$BA troll without his charm is like an orc without his battle scars...$B$BWorthless.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6481, 'enUS', 'You bear good news, $C! I fear the possibilities of what an Earthen would mean to Kalimdor.$B$BSlaying Goggeroc was a task for no one less than a hero. You have done well; all of Stonetalon and Kalimdor are indebted to you, noble $C.$B$BAccept this as your reward most honored one.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6482, 'enUS', 'You found my brother! He was captured by the Thistlefurs? That is terrible news to hear, for although many Furbolgs are noble creatures, the Thistlefurs are corrupt.$B$BThank you for rescuing my brother, $n. I do not want to think of how they treated poor Ruul. He will likely sleep long after this ordeal...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6503, 'enUS', 'Good, good!$B$BThe fewer \'a dem elves runnin\' around, the better.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6504, 'enUS', 'Reading isn\'t my strong point... but now I\'ll be able to get back to work! Thanks, $n!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6521, 'enUS', 'Good. Well done, $C.$B$BNow that Malcin is dead, we can at least know that the Scourges advances will be halted. I thank you for your efforts and wishes to reward you with a gift.$B$BAlthough we do not know the extent of the Scourges influence within the Downs, I am sure we will discover their plots soon enough.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6522, 'enUS', 'I recognize the insignia on this scroll, $n. You found this on that crone who reigns over Razorfen Kraul? Interesting.$B$BThe Scourge aren\'t content with one continent it seems. This Ambassador Malcin--the one who wrote the note--is one of the Scourge\'s plagued servants, a human diplomat to the kingdom of Lordaeron before things... changed.$B$BIf the Scourge are trying to gain a foothold in Kalimdor, then it is up to us to act.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6523, 'enUS', 'Kaya is alive! $n, I have you to thank for rescuing her.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6541, 'enUS', 'Ashenvale is a divided land, but our most recent efforts have been very successful. We not only have an outpost at the Zoram Strand, but another just north of here called Splintertree.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6542, 'enUS', 'Ashenvale is a divided land, but our most recent efforts have been very successful. We not only have an outpost at the Zoram Strand, but another just north of here called Splintertree.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6543, 'enUS', 'I can see that you are one that can be counted on. These updates are crucial to our plans to further our presence in Ashenvale. We can now plan our next move.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6544, 'enUS', 'So Torek\'s attack was successful! Well done, $n. Night elves are decent foes. A little skinny, but strong and fierce! I\'m sure the battle was something to see...$B$BAnd I hope you gained a scar or two!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6545, 'enUS', 'Well, my update will explain all of this to Kadrak. You must return this to him as quickly as possible.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6546, 'enUS', 'Take my update to Kadrak. Swiftly, $n.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6547, 'enUS', 'Let Kadrak know of the success we have had here holding off the night elves. Our plans are going well.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6548, 'enUS', '$n, I thank you... but I will never forget what the Grimtotem have done to my village.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6561, 'enUS', 'Kelris has eluded the Argent Dawn for some time.$B$BFor some time they considered him dead or missing.$B$BBy ending his reign you have spared the lives of many innocent people, $n.$B$BEarthmother be praised! To sacrifice another to a servant of an Old God for personal gain is beyond disgusting!$B$BYou have done a great thing this day. Kelris was a creature of evil and sought to bring the world back to a time of chaos by worshipping such creatures as the Old Gods. Thank you, $n.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6562, 'enUS', 'Tsunaman sent you? Excellent. Then we have matters to discuss.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6563, 'enUS', 'Well done, $n. These are the crystals I spoke of. Intriguing...$B$BI can feel the power within them. The spirits of water cling to them. Whatever the naga were going to use these for... well, let us be glad they are no longer in their hands.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6564, 'enUS', 'This is interesting indeed. I am glad you have brought it to my attention.$B$BNow we have a name for our troubles... Lorgus Jett.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6565, 'enUS', 'Very good!! Thank you, $n. We may not have stopped the Twilight\'s Hammer completely, but at least you have staved off another of their plans to return the Old Gods to power.$B$BWho knows what other plans they have manifesting, but we can rest easy for now.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6571, 'enUS', 'Excellent, $n. You\'ve saved me a lot of work!$B$BBut don\'t think that I\'m not grateful!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6581, 'enUS', 'This is perfect -- just the thing! Well, here\'s the shipment.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6603, 'enUS', 'Well, hi there! So Meggi told you of the trouble I have found here?', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6604, 'enUS', 'Aye, what can I do for you?', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6605, 'enUS', 'Ah, $C. I see that there is hope yet. Are you here to assist me?', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6607, 'enUS', 'Now that\'s a fine catch!$B$BCome over here, lemme show you how to set a few lines.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6608, 'enUS', '\'Course, you must be a friend of Lumak\'s.$B$BFishin\'? I can tell you all \'bout fishin\'.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6609, 'enUS', 'I\'ve always got room on my island for visitors... I reckon...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6610, 'enUS', 'You are in for a special treat, $n. Watch and learn!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6611, 'enUS', '<Dirge spits out some leather sandal bits.>$B$BPfftooey...$B$B<Dirge hacks loudly.>$B$BWhat? I\'ll have you know that leather is surprisingly high in protein and low in carbohydrates.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6612, 'enUS', '<Dirge spits out leather.>$B$BPfftey...$B$B<Dirge hacks loudly.>$B$BWhat? I\'ll have you know that leather is surprisingly high in protein and low in carbohydrates, $R.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6621, 'enUS', 'Good work, $n. Issuing that challenge to the Foulwealds and defeating their leader sends them a strong message:$B$BThe Horde is not to be trifled with.$B$BI don\'t believe that tribe will be giving us much trouble for a long time.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6622, 'enUS', 'Doctor $n, welcome to Horde Trauma.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6623, 'enUS', 'Wonderful. Put on your scrubs, we are to start at once!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6624, 'enUS', 'Doctor $n, welcome to Alliance Trauma.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6625, 'enUS', 'Wonderful. Put on your scrubs, we are to start at once!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6626, 'enUS', 'Thank you, $n! The work you\'ve done will be a great help, I\'m sure.$B$BI will continue my study of this diplomat and the rest of the quilboar here. If you seek greater adventure, I\'d find a few friends and head into the cave that looks like a great boar maw just over there. I\'m sure once you\'re inside you\'ll find greater challenges to face.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6627, 'enUS', 'Well done, $C. You have studied the text I asked you to, and now you have passed another of our tests.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6628, 'enUS', 'Well done, $n. I had my doubts if you studied the text I asked you to get, but you\'ve answered correctly.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6629, 'enUS', 'Grundig Darkcloud is dead! $n, I will always be grateful for what you\'ve done here today.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6641, 'enUS', 'I have witnessed many naga attacks since I arrived here. It puts my mind at ease that Vorsha will no longer roam freely.$B$BWe are in your debt, $n.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6642, 'enUS', 'Your offering has been accepted. Favor you have gained. Continue and you shall be allowed access to the ancient trades.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6643, 'enUS', 'Your offering has been accepted. Favor you have gained. Continue and you shall be allowed access to the ancient trades.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6644, 'enUS', 'Your offering has been accepted. Favor you have gained. Continue and you shall be allowed access to the ancient trades.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6645, 'enUS', 'Your offering has been accepted. Favor you have gained. Continue and you shall be allowed access to the ancient trades.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6646, 'enUS', 'Your offering has been accepted. Favor you have gained. Continue and you shall be allowed access to the ancient trades.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6661, 'enUS', 'These\'ll werk nicely, matey. Me brother needs em still tickin\' and kickin,\' else they go sour... Ye don\'t want to taste no sour rat kabob.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6662, 'enUS', 'Poor Monty. Ever since the Gnomeregan incident, he hasn\'t been the same. That boy has never seen an ocean in his life, let alone being some kind of pirate.$B$B<Nipsy sighs.>$B$BAt least he keeps the flow of twitching critters coming.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6681, 'enUS', 'Most excellent, young thief.$B$BYou look a bit beaten down, but no worse for the wear.$B$BA long journey awaits you - long and rewarding. Are you prepared to finally embrace your destiny among the masters of Ravenholdt?$B$BSpeak with the guards outside. They will get you started.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6701, 'enUS', 'Hey, nice work! Keep this up and the other rogues might stop spitting on you.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6741, 'enUS', 'Thanks again, $n. You do the Horde proud...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6761, 'enUS', 'Yes $C, thank you for coming. I apologize about the misunderstanding... the air is thick with mistrust between the Arch Druid here and Keeper Remulos in Moonglade. Each suspect the other of chicanery, and the fact that strange corruptions of Teldrassil continue unabated are still an issue here. It does little to quell mistrust.$B$BRegardless, our duty to the Cenarion Circle remains... even if those who lead it may disagree with one another.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6762, 'enUS', 'I am Rabine Saturna, and on behalf of Keeper Remulos and all of the denizens of this sacred glade I bid you welcome.$B$BI appreciate your interest and eagerness to assist the Cenarion Circle. I also know that Arch Druid of Darnassus expressed his displeasure to you in your lending us aid. Rest assured that it is for the greater good, and that you will be safe from any ill-conceived repercussions you may be the target of.$B$BYou are among friends here, $n.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6781, 'enUS', 'These are some good pieces, $n. I can use them to fashion new equipment for our troops.$B$BIf my supply level gets high enough, then maybe our seasoned fighting units will enter the field!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6801, 'enUS', 'The blood of our enemies has been shed. I shall mix this blood with the rest that has been gathered. Once the offering is complete, the Ice Lord shall show these Stormpike dogs the full wrath of the Frostwolf Clan!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6805, 'enUS', 'Your bravery is proven, as is your worth to us. Perhaps I may have future tasks for you, tasks more befitting a valued ally of the Waterlords.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6824, 'enUS', 'You have the hands! You defeated the fire captains! I would not have thought it possible, had I not known you and what you are capable of.$B$B$n, your exploits are without number, but word of this last feat will send waves among the Waterlords. Your name may one day be legend to us.$B$BSpeak with me again, $n. I may have yet another task...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6825, 'enUS', 'The fleet feeds on their flesh. It consumes the enemy.$B$BFlight is imminent!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6826, 'enUS', 'More! More! Bring more for they are soon to be ready!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6827, 'enUS', 'Not enough! I would expect this level of work from an initiate, but you, $n? Come on, soldier! HUSTLE! More flesh is needed!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6844, 'enUS', 'Well great monkey toads! What have you got here? It\'s sort of book shaped, I guess... I\'ll try and crack this shell on it.$B$BLayo sent you to me from Silithus? I\'ve only heard very hushed rumblings - which I guess aren\'t all that hushed when you think about it - about the horrors that are going on out there. Couple that with my lack of pleasure for anything bug-like, and you\'ve got the recipe for me needing to stay here with the books!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6845, 'enUS', 'Ah, $n - I had hoped you would stop by. I am glad to see you well.$B$BI received notice you would be coming in from the field, and I wanted to personally express the Cenarion Circle\'s gratitude for the assistance you\'ve given us thus far. No doubt there are more secrets to uncover from Silithus; your delivery to Umber should prove most interesting once uncovered. Please, accept this as a token of our continued appreciation for your aid.$B$BThank you, generous $C.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6881, 'enUS', 'Well done, $n. I will use the power of this charm to augment the magic that has already been gathered. When enough power has been amassed, I shall focus the collected energies and call upon the Forest Lord to aid our cause.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6921, 'enUS', 'This is exactly what I need! A fathom core is an incredible well of information that we will be able to draw much good from. Whatever the Twilight\'s Hammer is up to in there - and believe me when I say it is no good - my comrades and I will now uncover.$B$BYou\'ve done well here today; the Earthen Ring looks upon you warmly for assisting us. You\'ve also helped the Horde as a whole, and for that you should be proud.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6922, 'enUS', 'This... this is quite the find, $n.$B$BYou acquired this from Baron Aquanis in Blackfathom, you say? Baron Aquanis has long been thought of as a corrupted elemental power; this globe will prove what exactly had corrupted him. While it would be no surprise if it turned out to be the Twilight\'s Hammer, our studies will also show how they did it as well.$B$BYou did well in bringing this to me. Please - take this, along with the Earthen Ring\'s warmest regards.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6941, 'enUS', 'The flight will be ready soon. Continue your efforts!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6942, 'enUS', 'Keep em coming, soldier! The Aerie gryphons will be ready to strike in no time at all!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6943, 'enUS', 'Can you see it? Look at them, soldier! They\'re coming around... Soon, Ichman\'s flight will once again strike at the heart of the valley! Stormpike will rule the skies!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6961, 'enUS', 'Ho ho hello. I am Great-father Winter, and I - courtesy of the fine folks of Smokywood Pastures... \"Fresh from our farm to your plate, it\'s Smokywood Pastures wholesome goodness\" - would like to wish you a fantastic Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BIf you\'ve been good this year, maybe you will receive treats from Smokywood Pastures as your treat for the Feast of Winter Veil. Huzzah.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6962, 'enUS', 'You\'re quite the helper to ol\' Greatfather Winter there, $n. Have a great Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BHere\'s a little something... you know, for the effort.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6963, 'enUS', 'Y-y-you can h-h-hear me! Thank the b-b-bottom line!$B$BI\'m not really a s-s-snowman - my n-n-name is Sacks, and I w-w-work for the Orgrimmar b-b-branch of Smokywood Pastures... I g-g-got sent out here to look for a m-m-missing package, when I was attacked by a c-c-creature I have never seen b-b-before!$B$BSo v-v-very cold...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6964, 'enUS', 'The Feast of Winter Veil, you say? Alas, in times past it held a more substantial meaning to us tauren. Nowadays, it seems as though others have turned the legend of this season of renewal into something that helps to sell candies and presents.$B$BIt\'s no surprise that Furmund is bitter about that sort of change. He and other tauren like him cling to our past like a banner of war. While I think a little celebration is always good, it is important to remember the origins of the Feast.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6981, 'enUS', 'Oh... I have never seen anything like this...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6982, 'enUS', 'You got them! Well done, $n! I\'ll go through these supplies and get them ready for our own troops!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6983, 'enUS', 'You found it! You\'ve saved Smokywood Pasture\'s Feast of Winter Veil!$B$BYou\'re a true hero to everyone here at Smokywood Pastures and to all the children, of course!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6984, 'enUS', 'Ho ho hello, adventurer!$B$BThe goblins told me that you have earned a special gift this holiday season, and I am pleased to give it to you. Here you go - have a wondrous Feast of Winter Veil this and every season in the future.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (6985, 'enUS', 'You got them! Nicely done, $n! And I hope you saw a few dwarves during your raid, and shed their blood for the Frostwolves!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7001, 'enUS', 'I can only hope that those charged with collecting ram hides are as determined as you, $n.$B$BAt this rate, we will have the stables full in a matter of hours!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7002, 'enUS', 'Well done, soldier. I will notify you when I have stockpiled enough of the hides.$B$BCarry on!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7003, 'enUS', 'Splendifimous! Not only am I glad to see that you\'ve returned with the residue, but also with all your major appendages intact! That is, well, there was never any danger in using the Ultra-Shrinker, now was there!$B$BI do appreciate your effort on my behalf, $n. Truly, you are a friend to goblins everywhere. Accept this as a token of my appreciation!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7021, 'enUS', 'Ho ho hello. I am Great-father Winter, and I - courtesy of the fine folks of Smokywood Pastures... \"Fresh from our farm to your plate, it\'s Smokywood Pastures wholesome goodness\" - would like to wish you a fantastic Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BIf you\'ve been good this year, maybe you will receive treats from Smokywood Pastures as your treat for the Feast of Winter Veil. Huzzah.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7022, 'enUS', 'Ho ho hello. I am Greatfather Winter, and I - courtesy of the fine folks of Smokywood Pastures... \"Fresh from our farm to your plate, it\'s Smokywood Pastures wholesome goodness\" - would like to wish you a fantastic Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BIf you\'ve been good this year, maybe you will receive treats from Smokywood Pastures as your treat for the Feast of Winter Veil. Huzzah.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7023, 'enUS', 'Ho ho hello. I am Greatfather Winter, and I - courtesy of the fine folks of Smokywood Pastures... \"Fresh from our farm to your plate, it\'s Smokywood Pastures wholesome goodness\" - would like to wish you a fantastic Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BIf you\'ve been good this year, maybe you will receive treats from Smokywood Pastures as your treat for the Feast of Winter Veil. Huzzah.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7024, 'enUS', 'Ho ho hello. I am Greatfather Winter, and I - courtesy of the fine folks of Smokywood Pastures... \"Fresh from our farm to your plate, it\'s Smokywood Pastures wholesome goodness\" - would like to wish you a fantastic Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BIf you\'ve been good this year, maybe you will receive treats from Smokywood Pastures as your treat for the Feast of Winter Veil. Huzzah.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7025, 'enUS', 'You\'re quite the helper to ol\' Greatfather Winter there, $n. Have a great Feast of Winter Veil.$B$BHere\'s a little something... you know, for the effort.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7026, 'enUS', 'Well done, soldier. I will notify you when I have stockpiled enough of the hides.$B$BCarry on!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7027, 'enUS', 'The stables will be full in no time at all. Keep up the good work!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7028, 'enUS', 'Ha ha ha! I knew you\'d be back.$B$B<Willow mutters.>$B$B...So easy to convince.$B$B...Will do anything for the right price. Heh heh heh...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7029, 'enUS', 'Thank you for returning this, $n. With the remaining liquid you brought me, I can continue my studies.$B$BWhile there is still much to do, you have helped to heal some of the corruption that Vyletongue spread through Maraudon. Please take this with my gratitude.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7041, 'enUS', 'Thank you for returning this, $n. With the remaining liquid you brought me, I can continue my studies.$B$BWhile there is still much to do, you have helped to heal some of the corruption that Vyletongue spread through Maraudon. Please take this with my gratitude.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7042, 'enUS', 'Y-y-you can h-h-hear me! Thank the b-b-bottom line!$B$BI\'m not really a s-s-snowman - my n-n-name is Sacks, and I w-w-work for the Ironforge b-b-branch of Smokywood Pastures... I g-g-got sent out here to look for a m-m-missing package, when I was attacked by a c-c-creature I have never seen b-b-before!$B$BSo v-v-very cold...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7043, 'enUS', 'You found it! You\'ve saved Smokywood Pasture\'s Feast of Winter Veil!$B$BYou\'re a true hero to everyone here at Smokywood Pastures and to all the children, of course!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7044, 'enUS', 'Now that you have recovered the two parts of my scepter, I have hope that Maraudon may one day be rid of the Vyle corruption.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7045, 'enUS', 'Ho ho hello, adventurer!$B$BThe goblins told me that you have earned a special gift this holiday season, and I am pleased to give it to you. Here you go - have a wondrous Feast of Winter Veil this and every season in the future.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7046, 'enUS', 'Please take this, and know that the power allotted to you now must be used for good. Continue your journey through the caverns, and with hope, you will find the remains of my uncle. Much danger awaits you, $n.$B$BSpeak with me again should the need arise.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7061, 'enUS', 'The legends and lore surrounding the Winter Veil are ones that have faded from the forefront of public thought over the years. Yes, I know that the goblins are helping to revive the season for their own ends, the fact that our people reflect upon it at least in some form does good to keep such lore alive.$B$BYour desire to go beyond the material and learn about our past is an admirable trait, young $C. I salute your wisdom.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7062, 'enUS', 'The Feast of Winter Veil, you say? Alas, in times past it held a more substantial meaning to us dwarves. Nowadays, it seems as though others have turned the legend of Greatfather Winter into something that helps to sell candies and presents.$B$BIt\'s no surprise that Goli is bitter about that sort of change. He and other dwarves like him cling to our past like a banner of war. While I think a little celebration is always good, it is important to remember the origins of the Feast.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7063, 'enUS', 'The legends and lore surrounding the Winter Veil are ones that have faded from the forefront of public thought over the years. While I recognize that the goblins are helping to revive the season for their own ends, the fact that the citizenry thinks about it at least in some form does good to keep such lore alive.$B$BYour desire to go beyond the material and learn about our past is an admirable trait, young $C. I salute your erudite nature.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7064, 'enUS', 'This is most wonderful news, $n! Thank you!$B$BI will speak with Marandis and ask his wisdom on the topic of Zaetar\'s remains, but at least you have overcome the hardest of the tasks.$B$BI was told that if we were successful in our mission, I had permission to reward those who aided us. I was given these items as tokens from our people--you may choose one.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7065, 'enUS', 'This is most wonderful news, $n! Thank you!$B$BAlthough it concerns me that you were not able to bring back Zaetar\'s remains, who am I to question the will of Cenarius\' first born. Perhaps now the will of the centaur will break and their thirst for blood will lessen--we can only hope.$B$BIf successful in our mission, I was given these items to reward any who aided us. You may choose one as a token of thanks.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7066, 'enUS', 'So my brother has finally found peace? I am proud to have lived to see this day. In all his arrogance and anger, I truly thought he was lost to us, but this... this symbol of his sacrifice only proves that he is not lost--he has only been reborn. He takes his place in nature as was his duty.$B$BThank you, $n. By bringing this to me, you have secured a small amount of hope that I thought I had once lost. This seed will be important to the people of this war-torn land some day... I can sense it.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7067, 'enUS', 'This is it, $R! This is it! Now I can begin the great task of uniting the tribes. Thank you.$B$BTake this for your efforts, please. I hope when next we meet, it will be on much different terms.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7068, 'enUS', 'Ah, these be perfect for me magics. Here, you take one of these trinkets and be on your way... me got much studyin\' to do.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7070, 'enUS', 'These are perfect, $n. I actually had other adventurers return from there also and from them I was able to fashion these... please, feel free to take one for your hard work. And thank you again for more samples to study.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7081, 'enUS', 'Well done! Graveyards are vital to our control of Alterac Valley. When you capture one, you help ensure the Alliance\'s sovereignty here.$B$BGo now, $n. Reenter the battle, and if you see a graveyard under the Horde\'s control... you know what to do!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7082, 'enUS', 'Well done, $n! With each graveyard under our control, the spirits of our enemies will wander more lost and aimless.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7101, 'enUS', 'I heard of your mission\'s success! That pleases me...$B$BOur troops can now charge forward with impunity, and show the Alliance that Alterac Valley is no place for them!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7102, 'enUS', 'I received a field report stating you helped secure an enemy banner. Well done, $n! With their ranged troops out of position we can move the line of battle forward!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7121, 'enUS', 'It\'s good to see fresh troops here, $n, but with a little luck you\'ll get into some action and won\'t be fresh for long!$B$BSpeak with me again. I have tasks I must discuss with you....', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7122, 'enUS', 'You did it! Well done, $n!$B$BWhen we control a mine and have troops stationed there, it\'s much easier to gather minerals and supplies from it.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7123, 'enUS', 'Hail, $n! It is good to see a $C like yourself, eager to do his part for the Horde. Speak with me again, for I have vital tasks for you...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7124, 'enUS', 'You captured a mine! With our own warriors protecting it, it will be much simpler to extract minerals from its depths, or gather supplies that have been cached there.$B$BWell done, $n. The deed you have done is a great boon to our battle efforts.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7141, 'enUS', 'Well done, $n! With the Horde\'s nose bloodied after the death of their general, we\'ll have the breathing room we need to explore!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7142, 'enUS', 'Well done, $n! Stormpikes have no hope in this foolish invasion.$B$BHah! So far, all they\'ve done is get their general killed!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7161, 'enUS', 'That burning sensation you feel is your soul being awakened. Your spirit has accepted the call to arms.$B$BYou are now one of the Frostwolf, $n. Congratulations.$B$BCarry this insignia with you at all times. As you advance among the ranks of Frostwolf, I will replace the insignia with other, more powerful insignias.$B$BPerhaps someday you will be exalted among the Frostwolf Clan. Should that day ever come, you will be granted the Eye of Command.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7162, 'enUS', 'Take and wear this insignia with pride, $n. As your rank among the Stormpike grows, so too will the insignia. Return to me as you gain honor with Stormpike, and I shall replace your insignia with other, more powerful insignias.$B$BPerhaps someday you will grow to be a legend on this field of battle. Should that day ever come, you will be granted the Eye of Command.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7163, 'enUS', 'This new insignia reflects your rank amongst the Frostwolf. Keep it on you at all times.$B$BAnd $C... Die with honor!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7164, 'enUS', '<Warmaster Laggrond salutes.>$B$BGo, $n! Continue your defense of the Frostwolf. This war must be won! For Drek\'Thar! For the Warchief!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7165, 'enUS', '<Warmaster Laggrond roars.>$B$BThey have already begun telling tales of your deeds, soldier. The Stormpike shakes in fear when your name is uttered. Carry on!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7166, 'enUS', 'Soon, all on the field of battle will be under your watchful eye. Command of the Valley and its troops will be yours!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7167, 'enUS', 'Channel the power of the insignia. Let the enemy hear your words. The might of the Horde is unquestionable!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7168, 'enUS', 'Let our enemies see that a soldier of rank has struck them down! Fight for the glory of Stormpike!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7169, 'enUS', 'The king has been made aware of your battlefront heroics, $C. Continue in your stalwart defense of the Stormpike Guard!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7170, 'enUS', 'When we first met, I would have never guessed that a hero was in the making. Carry on, soldier!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7171, 'enUS', 'Surely it will be you who carries the Eye of Command!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7172, 'enUS', 'It is you who must lead our troops to victory, Commander! The soldiers are under your command. They will follow your direct orders. Lead them.... Crush the Frostwolf.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7201, 'enUS', 'Wonderful! I will have these sent by courier to the Undercity at once!$B$BAs for you - here is payment, as promised. Keep the change, you filthy beast!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7223, 'enUS', 'These are some good pieces, $n. I can use them to fashion new equipment for our troops.$B$BIf my supply level gets high enough, then maybe our seasoned fighting units will enter the field!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7224, 'enUS', 'These will do nicely. I\'ll melt them down and patch them up and you\'ll never know they came from those Stormpike cowards!$B$BThanks, $n. And let me polish up that armor of yours...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7241, 'enUS', 'To become a soldier of Frostwolf, one must first be tested...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7261, 'enUS', 'Let\'s get to work!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7321, 'enUS', 'My soothing turtle bisque will keep you warm on a cold night... if you care about that kind of thing.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7383, 'enUS', 'Along with the druids, the Oracle Tree has been carefully monitoring the growth of Teldrassil. Our observations have been disheartening, but all is not without hope.$B$BThe tree is indeed recovering since it\'s blessing, but the growth is still somehow stunted... hindered.$B$BWe suspect some portion of the corruption remains within the tree, waiting to be cleansed. We simply need to find it.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7385, 'enUS', 'The blood of our enemies has been shed. I shall mix this blood with the rest that has been gathered. Once the offering is complete, the Ice Lord shall show these Stormpike dogs the full wrath of the Frostwolf Clan!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7386, 'enUS', 'Well done, $n. I will use the power of these charms to augment the magic that has already been gathered. When enough power has been amassed, I shall focus the collected energies and call upon the Forest Lord to aid our cause.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7429, 'enUS', 'Oh, thank you for freeing me! You - ranked number one. Everyone else - ranked number two or lower.$B$BI knew my life was destined for more than just being an appetizer to some ogre!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7441, 'enUS', 'You have found it! A curse upon that miserable imp. Alas, my material possessions are meager at best. You may choose from what I have to offer.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7461, 'enUS', 'We thank you, hero.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7481, 'enUS', 'A shame... a tragedy. The items are lost you say? No trace of him, eh?', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7482, 'enUS', 'A shame... a tragedy. The items are lost you say? No trace of him, eh?', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7483, 'enUS', '<Lydros yawns.>$B$BAs promised, the Arcanum of Rapidity. Don\'t spend it all in once place.$B$B<Lydros snickers.>', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7484, 'enUS', 'Don\'t hurt yourself when applying the enchantment, $R.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7485, 'enUS', 'Yes, yes... Calm yourself. As promised, here is your Arcanum.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7486, 'enUS', 'Hydraxis\' voice descends from the waters\' surface...$B$B\"Choose that which best suits you, $n. May it protect you against the foes of the Waterlords.\"', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7488, 'enUS', 'You retrieved the web! Well done, $n! Lethtendris, like many elves of her ilk, are blind to the dangers the abuse of magic can cause to our world. They believe they are masters of magic; they do not realize that they are slaves to their own addiction. Her death saddens me, but it was necessary.$B$BThank you, $n. I will have the energies within the web released safely over a wide area, and then I\'ll destroy it to prevent future magical exploits.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7489, 'enUS', 'You have done well, $n. This web holds within it vast stores of the magic of Dire Maul, and I fear what damage may be unleashed if those energies were harnessed by one so irresponsible as Lethtendris. I am saddened by her death, but I know that she could never part with her web while alive.$B$BThank you, $n. I will send the web to students of magic more responsible than Lethtendris. They will be the new wardens of its power.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7490, 'enUS', 'This is a great victory for the Horde, $n. So many times you have honored your Warchief. It is time for the Warchief to honor you.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7491, 'enUS', 'Choose your reward and let the celebration of your glorious victory begin.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7492, 'enUS', 'Ah, it is good to see a $C heed my summons. I have need of your services, $n, and fear they will take you down a dangerous path...$B$BA path into Dire Maul.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7493, 'enUS', 'A dragon slayer and a seasoned leatherworker? You do not cease to astonish, hero. I am humbled.$B$BPlease accept what I am about to teach you. This knowledge will prove to be invaluable if you are to destroy what remains of the Black Dragonflight.$B$BCreate the cloak from the scales of the brood mother. It will protect you and your allies against the incendiary breath of the Lord of Blackrock... Nefarian.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7494, 'enUS', 'Hail, $n. I am pleased to see you, but regret that our meeting is not under more pleasant conditions.$B$BListen close, for I have a vital task for you...', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7495, 'enUS', 'Today, we celebrate this glorious victory!', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7496, 'enUS', 'Few are graced with such ceremony, $n. Please, choose your reward so that we may begin the celebration.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7497, 'enUS', 'A dragon slayer and a seasoned leatherworker? You do not cease to astonish, hero. I am humbled.$B$BPlease accept what I am about to teach you. This knowledge will prove to be invaluable if you are to destroy what remains of the Black Dragonflight.$B$BCreate the cloak from the scales of the brood mother. It will protect you and your allies against the incendiary breath of the Lord of Blackrock... Nefarian.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7498, 'enUS', 'Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7499, 'enUS', 'Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.', 0);
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward_locale` VALUES (7500, 'enUS', 'Excellent work, $R. Should you find any more tomes, do not hesitate to return them to us.$B$BAs time passes, we tend to change around and even add new rewards for the return of missing tomes.', 0);
